      <T n="text">0x73D5F30<!--Fairies are creatures that have a special connection to Emotions. In fact, their very existence depends on their unique Need: <font color="#199C2C"><b>Emotional Force</b></font>!\n\nFairies can replenish Emotional Force by:\n• <font color="#199C2C"><b>Absorbing Emotions</b></font> from another Sim.\n• Consuming <font color="#199C2C"><b>Emotion Potions</b></font> from <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary Crafting</b></font> or Aspiration Reward Store.\n• Using the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Regenerate Emotional Force</b></font> interaction on your Fairy Sim or their Fairy Home.\n\nFairies' Emotional Force is reduced by:\n• Natural depletion over time (Emotional Force does not deplete while Fairies are asleep.)\n• Using <font color="#199C2C"><b>Fairy Abilities.</b></font>--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_FairyOccultEmotionalForce_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:9acadf474d54c1ef</T>
      <T n="text">0xBC9E918B<!--When a Fairy's <font color="#199C2C"><b>Emotional Force</b></font> is too low, they will become <font color="#199C2C"><b>Emotionally Starving.</b></font> If they remain Emotionally Starving for too long they will eventually become <font color="#199C2C"><b>Emotionally Ravenous</b></font>, which is extremely dangerous to their health!\n\nThe Fairy's Emotional Force Need color will change in both scenarios, and they will have a Moodlet relating to each stage of starvation. If a Fairy Sim is Emotionally Ravenous and their motive completely depletes, they will die of <font color="#199C2C"><b>Emotional Starvation</b></font>.--></T>
    </U>
